 where the SN Ia explosion is not triggered by the helium- or\ncarbon-ignition during the merger. The merger ejecta interact with the\nsurrounding interstellar medium, and form a shell. The shell has a bolometric\nluminosity of more than $2 \\times 10^{35}$ ergs$^{-1}$ lasting for $\\sim 2\n\\times 10^4$ yr. If this is the case, Milky Way should harbor about $10$ such\nshells at any given time.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 23 Apr 2015 03:41:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-04-24"}
